The paper deals with the task of pixel-wise semantic segmentation, which is a common problem in computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of Random Forests and Neural Networks, which are popular machine learning techniques, indicating that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the construction and initialization of deep CNNs, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the application of the techniques to microscopy images, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
